725497f-a.text:
58th Street, east side, north from Woodside Avenue, showing a group of old mansions. The thoroughfare was formerly called
Fifth Street.
P. L. Sperr  October 27, 1931

725496f-a.text:
58th Street, east side, between Woodside and 39th Avenues, showing the mansion which was owned by N.Terret in 1891. 58th
Streot, here, was then named Fifth Street.
P. L. Sperr  October 27, 1931

728230f-a.text:
58-07 Woodside Avenue, north side, between 58th and 59th Streets, showing an old home, about 175 feet back of
the normal building line.
P. L. Sperr  November 5, 1931
